name: Neil Singer
text: They always make tasty pizza here, but the time it takes to get your order ready can vary greatly.  I was told to expect a 15 minute wait, but the actual wait was 50 minutes for today's order.  On the positive side, it was delicious.

name: Matt Valuk
text: One of the best Papa Gino's in the area. The pizza is consistently good and not greasy.  The service is consistently great.  My son loves the duck claw game.

name: peace searcher
text: Pizza sauce tasted fair. Didn't think the integrity of the slice stood up.  Needed to put a lot of oregano and parmesan cheese on it.  I like going into joints just to get a couple of slices. I mean it was a quick lunch I'll let this pass.

name: Patricia Desjardins
text:
Ordered the Patriots special.
Chicken came out barely warm. Pizza was stiff like cardboard and ever so slightly warm. Even after adding Parmesan cheese and oregano there was little flavor.
Frequent customer of different Papa Gino‚Äôs.

text: Place is terrible. Brought food to the wrong address then asked if I could come pick it up at the store. Pizza was cold and two hours late. The sauce tasted expired and the cheese had mold on it. On top of all that there was a curly black hair in the pizza. They wouldn't even give me a refund. never eat here worst pizza place around

text: Decent food. Enjoyed the salad. Actually i was pleasantly surprised.

text: Surprisingly outstanding service. The staff really went above and beyond for us. The food is fine.

text: I like to pop in here for the lunch specials since it's close to work. Always have a good experience here and love the window seats up front.

name: Jo Ta
text: I like Papa Gino's pizza. This location though it pretty bad. I have had many different experience there but no consistency. The bad experiences out weight the good. ‚Ä¶More

name: April O'Patchen
text: Literally the worst pizza I've ever tasted. We moved here from florida and wanted to try a northern chain or whatever this papa gino's is... the sauce tastes like they squeezed the juice from a tomato and then watered it down and threw it on the pizza. Even the cheese tastes watered down. 0 flavor and the crust sucks.

name: Sara Lamb
text: They lost my order, after the pizza was 20 minutes late I called. They said they couldn't find it.  The manager offered nothing but "rushing" the order which would be ANOTHER hour.  I cancelled my order, just moved into the area and they lost a pizza eating family's business!  NO costumer service!

name: A Stygles
text: Their pizza used to be a bit so-so, but the strong oregano flavors help it. The crust is a little thick, however, and is the weakest point. The plain wings were surprisingly good.

name: Deborah Copson
